cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SI 

The paper discusses attacks against generative models using GANs, which are commonly used in computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also focuses on datasets of complex representations of faces (LFW), objects (CIFAR-10), and medical images (Diabetic Retinopathy), which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the sensitivity of the attacks to different training parameters and mitigation strategies, which could also place it in the sub-category cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
